  "text": "Ezrin is known to be a component of cell-surface structures that are involved in cell adhesion to the extracellular matrix, as well as in cell-cell interactions, receptor tyrosine-kinase signaling, signal transduction through Rho GTPase and interactions with the Aktmediated cellular apoptotic machinery [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
